wAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=199.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_supermad.gif" align=absmiddle>  /guildremove XXXX</span><hr size=1> Ok... I just thought I'd see what others think about this situation... This may be a little long, but there are details I need to convey, so please bear with me.<br>
<br>
I am the Guild Leader of Outcast Realm.  The other night one of my officers sent me a tell about a potential new member who was looking for a guild.  The guy was 50ish and we were somewhat suspicious of him not having a guild already.  After we talked about it a bit (the officer and I) we decided to give this guy a shot as his reason for not having a guild seemed reasonable enough.  Welcome to the guild was soon seen on /gu.  <br>
<br>
Everything was fine for about 22 hours.  Then the fun began...<br>
<br>
I suddenly received a number of tells from a group in EW asking if I was an officer of my guild.  I responded that I was the Guild Leader, and asked how I could help them.  I was informed that this new member was KS'ing and camp stealing, and ended up intentionally training this group with an Elite because they would not give up a camp, which resulted in deaths of all their party members.  I immediately looked to see if the accused was online to hear his side of the story and found that he was not (suspicious clue #2).  I got the details of the situation from a couple of the people in the group involved, the story from a couple of them, the names of all of the group, and I offered to get them Rez's.  They were ok on the rez's and I said that I would address this with the accused guild member as soon as he was online.  I informed the group that this was a new member, and that I had no issues removing them should the evidence lead me to believe they were being truthful.  <br>
<br>
Hours passed, and the accused person finially logged back on.  I began discussing this with him and he of course said that they trained him.  Their story was that they had camped this location for a few hours and the accused showed up telling them to leave, and when they would not, he pulled an Elite on them.  His story was that he was there first, and was helping a friend near their camp, and they trained the Elite on him and his friend resulting in the death of his friend and him zoning with 12 hps left.  Unfortunately, there was no real way to verify either story, but with a number of people saying one thing, and one new, unknown guild member saying another, I tended to lean to believing the group.   In addition some of the accused's facts did not really seem to add up.  I discussed this with the accused, and even HE SAID that probably the only solution was him to /guildremove.  I apologized that things had come to this, and stated that I would not speak of him badly, but it would be in the best intrest of the guild if he would /guildremove.  He did this himself, and everthing seemed fine.  <br>
<br>
Shortly later, the same night, the fun began...  I got accused of calling him a liar, which I never did, and he threatened to train on everyone that was in the group accusing him.  He demanded the names of the accusers, which I would not provide.  I told him to let it go and we would also.  As far as those involved, other than him, it was a closed issue.  He logged shortly after, and came back as an alt in another guild.  Again the /tell began, and he even got his guild officers from the alt's guild involved.  I explained the situation to them, and was told they would talk to the guild leader about it.  At this point I realized that I had made the right decision in getting him out of the guild.<br>
<br>
The next night my guild informed me that this guy had started up again.  He was threatening everyone in the guild, directly, with trains.  And wanted to duel everyone.  One of my members who was not aware of the previous events dueled him and of course the accused ran for the zone when things wern't going his way.  The flames kept up even being /ooc'd to the zone.  They really got out of hand from what I hear.  <br>
<br>
This is still going on to a certain extent.  <br>
<br>
My reason for this post is twofold.  First, was I out of line in asking a new unknown member to leave the guild because of these accusations?  Secondly, I felt the need to post this as a way to provde information to those who may have heard about this situation, and to protect the name of Outcast Realm.  We in no way support any member of our guild violating the rules, both written and unwritten, of EQ regarding trains, KS, and camps.  I have never had any complaints regarding the guild since my assuming the role of leader (a few months), and we pride ourselves in helping others including those not in our guild.<br>
<br>
Again, sorry for the long post, but I'm curious what others think.  <br>
<br>
Keevian<br>
